President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts in the J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board. The appointees include Mark C. Alexander, a Professor of Law at Seton Hall University School of Law; Mark Brzezinski, a partner at McGuireWoods specializing in anti-corruption law; Lisa M. Caputo, Managing Director at Citigroup's Investment Bank; and Shelby F. Lewis, Professor Emeritus at Clark Atlanta University and an international development consultant. President Obama expressed confidence in the appointees' experience and expertise and looks forward to working with them in the future.